results.description:
Where: North Cascades
Length: 10.4 miles roundtrip
Elevation Gain: 1400 feet

Difficulty: Easy, a pleasant trail with a steep but short climb to the lake

Northwest Forest Pass required

7:00 AM: Meet at the Ash Way P&R to arrange carpools if needed. GO TO THE BUS STOPS, NORTH END OF PARK & RIDE (Imagine I-5 North and follow the direction when you try to find the north end of P&R)

8:30 AM: Arrive at the trailhead, start hiking

12 PM: Lunch by the lake

1 PM: Start heading back to the cars

3:30-4 PM: Drive back to Lynnwood

6: PM: Arrive at the Ash Way P&R

Optional: Dinner in Granite Falls

A nice hike with plenty of variety. Beautiful forest, a rushing creek, waterfalls of all shapes and sizes, history, and of course a large blue-green lake surrounded by snowy peaks. At 10.4 miles, it can be either a day-hike or a quick early season overnight.

The trail starts at the far end of the large parking lot. In just a few minutes, come to a well signed junction for the Upper Elliot and Lower Elliot trails. They’ll rejoin in approximately three miles, so the choice is yours.

The trail to the right drops down to the creek. You will be on a twisty trail surrounded by conifers, alders, ferns and skunk cabbage. The first mile or so is close enough to hear the creek and periodically enjoy peek-a-boo views of it. The tread is soft, and the stream crossings are small with stepping stones that may be partially submerged in the early season.

Shortly after the trails rejoin, the way gets a little rocky and the grade steepens. As you switchback up the hillside, keep your eyes and ears open for a large waterfall on your right. Continuing uphill, arrive at the root-ball of a large fallen tree. The trail switchbacks to the left here, but the adventurous will want to take a quick side trip to the right. There was once an old wood-planked road here and a bridge across the river to an old town site. The bridge is gone, but there is still a rushing waterfall worth visiting. You’ll have to contend with some fallen trees, but none of them are too bad.

After a bit more climbing, reach a well-signed junction just before the lake. The campsites and two open-air privies are to the left. There are at least 15 sites here, though none of them are particularly private. The forest is open and the camp resembles a terraced hillside. The trail to the lake continues to the right. After a short distance, arrive at a signed day-use area. This is your best bet for a lunch overlooking the lake, or for letting your kids run around. Even though the trail is popular, there is some room to spread out here.

Driving Directions
Take the Mountain Loop Highway east from Granite Falls. Pass by the Verlot Ranger Station, where you can buy a Northwest Forest Pass if you need one. Continue to the end of the pavement, and then go another 3.5 miles. Turn right at the road signed "Elliot and Goat Lakes." This is FR-4080, but the road number is not clearly marked. The parking lot is at the end of the good gravel road.

Please prepare $15 for your driver and a plastic bag for you muddy boots.

Two no-shows and/or late cancellations and you wouldn"t be able to participate in my future events.

results.description:
It"s high time that there"s a weekly get-together that dads and their families can count on! Join us every Thursday in West Seattle at the High Point Family Center for an opportunity to let the kiddos and dads get out of the house and socialize!

For the Kiddos: the Family Center is a magnificent space to let the little ones play in. With toys, crafts and instruments to spare, it is a secure and active space for children and infants of all stages to excel in.


For the Dads: Coffee and snacks, computers, a widescreen TV, all at your disposal. Other dads to meet and relate to.

Free Childcare: At times we will provide short-term childcare within the (secure) Family Center during workshops, classes, speakers or other on-site parenting opportunities arise. It can also be provided for those who need to take a breather, make an important phone call, etc., as long as dad is still onsite. If you need childcare during drop-in hours, please contact Will.


All drop-in services are FREE. Please contact Will if you have any questions, comments or ideas. Hope to see you there!

results.description:
PLEASE NOTE - we"re in the process of Chartering and are now accepting applications for membership. We"re a "Category closed" group, meaning one person per business/market. We have filled the following categories:


Residential Realtor, Social Media Manager, Property & Casualty Insurance, Signage & Graphics, Photographer, General Contractor, doTerra Oils & Essentials

https://youtu.be/72zC1lYUmXc

We meet every 1st and 3rd Thursday of each month. We ask that members & guests show up by no later than 11:45 in order to place food order & be seated!


Come experience #thePNAway! We"re growing fast and looking for Small Business owners (or their employees) who are looking to grow their businesses by connecting with other like-minded entrepreneurs.

This is not just a social event! Read below to familiarize yourself with how we run our meetings! This is our first LUNCH group, and we"re excited to change things up a bit with this new daytime venue!

Our meetings begin with a President and a Vice President"s report, then we get into our 45 second commercials. This is a chance for you to introduce yourself, your business, what you do, what a good referral would be for you, and any new or interesting information about your company.

Every meeting, members are on the speaker rotation and 2 presentations are given. This gives each member the opportunity to speak for 8 minutes in more detail about their business or a particular topic of their choice. We then do some quick, structured brain-storming on how we can help the speaker"s business.

We finish by passing referrals, giving testimonials or a quick commercial for yourself again and then wrap things up!!

We"re a really fun, laid-back yet professional group that loves to get together and help each others" business. We highly encourage referrals and one-on-one meetings between members. And because we"re all professionals, we don"t see the need for fines or penalties for "breaking the rules." PNA is a great group of people who want to grow our businesses, learn from one another, and enjoy getting together.

Drop by a meeting anytime and see what we"re about!
results.how_to_find_us: We"re located on Bothell-Everett Hwy approximately 1.5 miles past Thrasher"s Corner!
results.name: Come Experience Networking done RIGHT! #thePNAway

meta.description: Searches for recent and upcoming public events hosted by Meetup groups. Its search window  is the past one month through the next three months, and is subject to change. Open Events is optimized to search for current events by location, category, topic, or text, and only lists Meetups that have **3 or more RSVPs**. The number or results returned with each request is not guaranteed to be the same as the page size due to secondary filtering. If you"re looking for a particular event or events within a particular group, use the standard [Events](/meetup_api/docs/2/events/) method.
